                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="14210" author="laisiyao" created="Wed, 11 May 2011 19:14:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;clio has implemented this functionality, nothing needs to be done for master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14207" author="jay" created="Wed, 11 May 2011 19:03:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree with tappro.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13917" author="tappro" created="Sat, 7 May 2011 02:02:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The echo_client uses obd_brw() only for &apos;disk&apos; mode, e.g. when echo client is sitting on top of obdfilter, so there is no network requests at all.&lt;br/&gt;
In network mode the cl_echo_object_brw() is used and it is asynchronous. Therefore is must have multiple RPCs in flight. Maybe there is another reason for bad performance?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
